The key insight in this problem is to recognize that each segment $\overline{P_kQ_k}$ forms a right-angled triangle similar to the original triangle $ABC$. This allows us to express the length of each segment as a fraction of the diagonal's length, depending on the value of $k$. By observing that these lengths form an arithmetic sequence, we can efficiently calculate their sum using the formula for the sum of an arithmetic sequence.
